   Program Summary: Program Direction

   Vision Statement
   Provide knowledge and innovative technologies that lead to new and
   expanded market opportunities for United States agriculture

   Mission Statement
   To enhance the economic viability and competitiveness of U.S.
   agriculture by maintaining the quality of harvested agricultural
   commodities or otherwise enhancing their marketability, meeting
   consumer needs, developing environmentally friendly and efficient
   processing concepts, and expanding domestic and global market
   opportunities through the development of value-added food and nonfood
   products and processes.

   Research Components
     * Quality Characterization, Preservation, and Enhancement
     * New Processes, New Uses, and Value-Added Biobased Products
